atin: in addition to the expression  (modelled on ), an unusual structure for Sicilian Greek inscriptions occurs, in which the invocation to the underworld spirits is followed by the name of the dedicant (often with an attribute), by the name of the deceased in dative, by the dedication verb and by the age of the deceased (see Korhonen 2004: 88). In this case, the relative pronoun introduces the age of the deceased with a  since the gender of the referent () and the relative pronoun do not correspond. The use of  to indicate the deceased, who died at the age of 27, is also peculiar: on the use of  in other epitaphs from Catania, generally referring to children, see IMusCatania 67 = , IMusCatania 140 = . On the use of  as a possessive pronoun, see also IG 14.485 = .",[588,590,592,594,596,597,598],{"_":589,"xml:lang":126},"Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)",{"_":591,"xml:lang":385},"D(iis) M(anibus) s(acrum)",{"_":593,"xml:lang":385},"costructio ad sensum",{"_":595,"xml:lang":126},"τέκνον",{"_":595,"xml:lang":126},{"_":595,"xml:lang":126},{"_":599,"xml:lang":126},"ἴδιος",[601,604,607],{"_":602,"target":603},"ISic001306","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001306",{"_":605,"target":606},"ISic003260","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003260",{"_":608,"target":609},"ISic001308","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001308",{"type":611,"listBibl":612},"bibliography",[613,635],{"type":129,"bibl":614},[615,620,623,626,629,632],{"type":132,"n":133,"citedRange":616,"ptr":618,"ref":619},{"ref":617},{"_":136,"target":137},{"target":139},{"_":141,"target":141},{"type":132,"n":145,"citedRange":146,"ptr":621,"ref":622},{"target":148},{"_":150,"target":150},{"type":132,"n":154,"citedRange":155,"ptr":624,"ref":625},{"target":157},{"_":159,"target":159},{"author":163,"date":164,"citedRange":165,"ptr":627,"ref":628},{"target":167},{"_":169,"target":169},{"author":163,"date":173,"citedRange":174,"ptr":630,"ref":631},{"target":176},{"_":178,"target":1