ref=\"ISic001299_fr2_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 13.05.2016\" src=\"ISic001299_fr2_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001299_fr2_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 13.05.2016\" src=\"ISic001299_fr2_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001299_fr3_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 13.05.2016\" src=\"ISic001299_fr3_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001299_fr3_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 13.05.2016\" src=\"ISic001299_fr3_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001299_fr4_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 13.05.2016\" src=\"ISic001299_fr4_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001299_fr4_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 13.05.2016\" src=\"ISic001299_fr4_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΘΚΙ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΖΩΤΙΚΟΣΠΑΤΗΡ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΙΔΙΩΤΕΚΝΩΜΝΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΗΣΧΑΡΙΝΕΠΟΙΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΣΕΝΟΣΕΖΗΣΕΝΕΕ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al6\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ivy-leafΚ\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">Η\u003C/span>´\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ivy-leaf\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Biscari, Torremuzza, Franz: Ἰ(ούλιος) Ζωτικὸς; Ferrara, Kaibel, Korhonen: Ζωτικὸς\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Biscari, Ferrara, Kaibel, Korhonen τέκνῳ; Torremuzza, Franz: τέκνῃ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>ΕΕΤΗ lapis (although Korhonen reports FFTH, considering this linguistic interference; the reading is unclear from photograph due to modern repainting of letters)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 6\">line.6: \u003Cspan>Biscari, Torremuzza, Ferrara, Franz, Kaibel could see a Η and a second ivy leaf at line end, now lost.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sacred to the subterranean deities. Zotikos, the father, made it for the sake of the memory for his own child, who lived for 27 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sacro alle divinità sotterranee. Zotico, il padre, ha realizzato per la memoria di suo figlio, che visse 27 anni.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp> This pagan epitaph is influenced by Latin: in addition to the expression \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)\u003C/span> (modelled on \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">D(iis) M(anibus) s(acrum)\u003C/span>), an unusual structure for Sicilian Greek inscriptions occurs, in which the invocation to the underworld spirits is followed by the name of the dedicant (often with an attribute), by the name of the deceased in dative, by the dedication verb and by the age of the deceased (see Korhonen 2004: 88). In this case, the relative pronoun introduces the age of the deceased with a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">costructio ad sensum\u003C/span> since the gender of the referent (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τέκνον\u003C/span>) and the relative pronoun do not correspond. The use of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τέκνον\u003C/span> to indicate the deceased, who died at the age of 27, is also peculiar: on the use of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τέκνον\u003C/span> in other epitaphs from Catania, generally referring to children, see IMusCatania 67 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001306\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001306\u003C/a>, IMusCatania 140 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003260\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003260\u003C/a>. On the use of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἴδιος\u003C/span> as a possessive pronoun, see also IG 14.485 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001308\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001308\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0476\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 148 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 3.5708 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1769 151 no. 34 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1784 159 no. 37 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 348 no. 3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 88 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[652,654,656,658,660,662,664],{"id":129,"html":653},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΘΚΙ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΖΩΤΙΚΟΣΠΑΤΗΡ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΙΔΙΩΤΕΚΝΩΜΝΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΗΣΧΑΡΙΝΕΠΟΙΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΣΕΝΟΣΕΖΗΣΕΝΕΕ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al6\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ivy-leafΚ\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">Η\u003C/span>´\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ivy-leaf\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":561,"html":655},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Biscari, Torremuzza, Franz: Ἰ(ούλιος) Ζωτικὸς; Ferrara, Kaibel, Korhonen: Ζωτικὸς\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Biscari, Ferrara, Kaibel, Korhonen τέκνῳ; Torremuzza, Franz: τέκνῃ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>ΕΕΤΗ lapis (although Korhonen reports FFTH, considering this linguistic interference; the reading is unclear from photograph due to modern repainting of letters)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 6\">line.6: \u003Cspan>Biscari, Torremuzza, Ferrara, Franz, Kaibel could see a Η and a second ivy leaf at line end, now lost.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":579,"html":657},"\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sacred to the subterranean deities. Zotikos, the father, made it for the sake of the memory for his own child, who lived for 27 years.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":579,"html":659},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sacro alle divinità sotterranee. Zotico, il padre, ha realizzato per la memoria di suo figlio, che visse 27 anni.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":584,"html":661},"\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp> This pagan epitaph is influenced by Latin: in addition to the expression \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)\u003C/span> (modelled on \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">D(iis) M(anibus) s(acrum)\u003C/span>), an unusual structure for Sicilian Greek inscriptions occurs, in which the invocation to the underworld spirits is followed by the name of the dedicant (often with an attribute), by the name of the deceased in dative, by the dedication verb and by the age of the deceased (see Korhonen 2004: 88). In this case, the relative pronoun introduces the age of the deceased with a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">costructio ad sensum\u003C/span> since the gender of the referent (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τέκνον\u003C/span>) and the relative pronoun do not correspond. The use of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τέκνον\u003C/span> to indicate the deceased, who died at the age of 27, is also peculiar: on the use of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">τέκνον\u003C/span> in other epitaphs from Catania, generally referring to children, see IMusCatania 67 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001306\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001306\u003C/a>, IMusCatania 140 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003260\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003260\u003C/a>. On the use of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἴδιος\u003C/span> as a possessive pronoun, see also IG 14.485 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001308\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001308\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":611,"html":663},"\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0476\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 148 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 3.5708 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1769 151 no. 34 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1784 159 no. 37 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 348 no. 3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 88 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  ",{"id":665,"html":666},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[668,670,672,674,676,678,680,682,684,686,688,690,692,694,696,698],{"image":106,"thumb":669,"title":107},"ISic001299_fr1_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":459,"thumb":671,"title":460},"ISic001299_fr1-thumb.jpg",{"image":462,"thumb":673,"title":107},"ISic001299_fr1_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":464,"thumb":675,"title":460},"ISic001299_fr1_copy2-thumb.jpg",{"image":466,"thumb":677,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr2_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":471,"thumb":679,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr2-thumb.jpg",{"image":473,"thumb":681,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr3_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":475,"thumb":683,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr3-thumb.jpg",{"image":477,"thumb":685,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr4_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":479,"thumb":687,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr4-thumb.jpg",{"image":484,"thumb":689,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr2_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":486,"thumb":691,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr2_rear-thumb.jpg",{"image":488,"thumb":693,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr3_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":490,"thumb":695,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr3_rear-thumb.jpg",{"image":492,"thumb":697,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr4_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":494,"thumb":699,"title":469},"ISic001299_fr4_rear-thumb.jpg"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
